        "type": "website",
        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: The best sci-fi books like Dune | Kobo Books Blog\nurl: \"https://www.kobo.com/blog/epic-scifi-books-for-fans-of-dune-1\"\ndescription: \"A hybrid of fantasy and science fiction, the extensive and considered world-building throughout this award-winning trilogy appeals to readers across the spectrum of speculative fiction. The apocalyptic tale it tells is grim, imbued with recognizable but re-imagined themes of race and social power dynamics, set against the looming disaster of a changing climate. View eBook · A military story with a twist, Scalzi's series explores themes of friendship, identity, and what it means to be human in a time of interplanetary travel and colonization. At the same time, it's an action-packed ride through outer space facilitated by technology that's a delight to imagine as being just ahead of us.\"\npage_age: \"May 29, 2025\"\nprofile_name: Rakuten Kobo\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/zpJ_hkVbvC2RxfWnMHIoFxuF9XI1X41vr0Qo6rWkD24/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvMTVjY2Q1M2Yx/N2M5MDdjZjQyYmRh/M2UwMThjMzU2Nzgx/YTU3MTgwNDhlZmM2/NDQxYTYzY2ZlY2E3/NmYyMzQyOS93d3cu/a29iby5jb20v\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/3VEl81DVQaPlXiBdVlm8rHx0yRLpoBPlSsgWsHVfYS8/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9rb2Jv/LWJsb2cudHJhbnNm/b3Jtcy5zdmRjZG4u/Y29tL3Byb2R1Y3Rp/b24vYXNzZXRzL2Nv/dmVycy9kdS1mcC0w/MDIuanBnP3c9MTIw/MCZhbXA7aD02MzAm/YW1wO3E9ODImYW1w/O2F1dG89Zm9ybWF0/JmFtcDtmaXQ9Y3Jv/cCZhbXA7ZG09MTcw/Njg5ODIwNyZhbXA7/cz1kZWNkNzJlMjVi/M2JmMjFkNDNhODA5/NGQ1YzFjMjc5OA\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://kobo-blog.transforms.svdcdn.com/production/assets/covers/du-fp-002.jpg?w=1200&amp;h=630&amp;q=82&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;dm=1706898207&amp;s=decd72e25b3bf21d43a8094d5c1c2798\"\nextra_snippets: \"Under threat of attack by gigantic sandworms, a natural resource necessary for space travel (which also happens to have narcotic qualities) is extracted by order of the distant and mysterious Emperor. Dune is a masterwork of science fiction, powered by a captivating story of environmental exploitation, politics, colonialism, and religion.|A hybrid of fantasy and science fiction, the extensive and considered world-building throughout this award-winning trilogy appeals to readers across the spectrum of speculative fiction. The apocalyptic tale it tells is grim, imbued with recognizable but re-imagined themes of race and social power dynamics, set against the looming disaster of a changing climate. View eBook · A military story with a twist, Scalzi's series explores themes of friendship, identity, and what it means to be human in a time of interplanetary travel and colonization. At the same time, it's an action-packed ride through outer space facilitated by technology that's a delight to imagine as being just ahead of us.|Readers hungry for even more epic science fiction can turn their sandworm-sized appetites to the books the aforementioned movies and TV shows are based on—or some of the books below that Hollywood hasn't yet mined.|A science fiction classic from the 1940s, Foundation is truly a tale of epic proportions. Asimov’s stories are known for their incredible foresight, and while set to a galactic backdrop, at its heart this series is really about the rise and fall of human societies.\"\nhash: e7c153186456b68a\nembed_ref: kobo.com-edY\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
